This code file contains a scraper designed to crawl the entire tamucc.edu domain.
It automatically discovers every hyperlink inside the domain, scrapes the content, extracts PDFs, follows unlimited pagination, and stores all content in a JSON Lines (JSONL) dataset for downstream use in LLM training or embedding vector stores (FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma, etc).

--> How It Works: 
1. Start from the root URL https://www.tamucc.edu/
2. Add this URL to to_visit queue
3. Pop URLs from queue one at a time
4. For each URL:
Request URL
Detect type (HTML or PDF)
Extract text accordingly
Append extracted result to memory list
Parse HTML to discover new internal links
5. Detect pagination patterns and push them to queue
6. Continue until there are no more new URLs on domain
7. All collected documents are stored in scraped_data.jsonl

Requirements Needed:
pip install requests beautifulsoup4 lxml numpy tqdm PyPDF2 retrying
